description.plain:
Florida Georgia Line is an American country music duo composed of Brian Kelley and Tyler Hubbard. Their name is derived from Brian and Tyler’s home states of Florida and Georgia, respectively.

On July 16, 2012, Florida Georgia Line signed with Big Machine Records.

description.plain: Country’s version of a “we’re young, proud of how we were raised, and just wanna have fun” song.  The FL-GA boys tell you how they like to have a good time with a little backing from another Georgia boy, Luke Bryan.  The official video also features a cameo from Travis Pastrana and his Nitro Circus.
